race.comment: ROYAL TESTAMENT (8) made it back-to-back wins when successful last start over 1106m in stakes class at Colonial Downs (Turf), getting home by 4 lengths. Meets a stronger field but she is good enough to score again. SNOW FACE PRINCESS (6) was flying with two wins in a row before being sent out favourite last time and finishing second over 1308m at Kentucky. Hard to knock and is a winning chance. JUST PHILTORED (3) went forward and proved too strong last time out, scoring by 4.5 lengths over 1106m in Listed grade at Colonial Downs (Turf). Will again be prominent from the outset. Meeting a deeper field this time but she deserves plenty of thought. OSCAR'S ENCORE (1) ran sixth at her latest appearance over 1609m at Kentucky, finishing 3 lengths from the winner. Right in the contest.
